    affiliation: "Department of Biochemistry, University of Otago"
repository-code: "https://github.com/zz153/GBM_Neoantigen_Pipeline"
url: "https://github.com/zz153/GBM_Neoantigen_Pipeline"
abstract: |
  A data-driven computational pipeline for identifying evolutionarily stable
  neoantigen targets in IDH-wildtype glioblastoma through integrated genomic
  filtering and HLA prediction. The pipeline filters somatic mutations based
  on clonality (VAF > 0.4), expression (TPM > 10), and frequency (≥10 patients),
  then predicts HLA class I and class II binding using NetMHCpan tools.
keywords:
  - glioblastoma
  - neoantigens
  - immunotherapy
  - HLA prediction
  - tumor evolution
  - clonality
  - cancer genomics
  - bioinformatics
  - NetMHCpan
  - TCGA
